data.title: It's all about the experience
data.text: Food was nothing to brag to mom about...but the staff sure was, that is a good enough reason to come back and try something else on the menu.  Our group of 15, was seated and served with the speed of a party of 2.  Worth a shot...one from the bar and another at the food.

data.title: Yummy Sunday Brunch Mimosas
data.text: Everybody in our party of 8 loved their sunday brunch.  The food and service was great, and you can't beat the endless mimosas for a great price.  The mimosas even come with a great fruit plate and dessert, and they are poured with a nice proportion of champagne to orange juice...no skimping.  For whatever reason, this place is not busy or crowded either so there is no wait and you can sit wherever you want with a great view of downtown.  We'll definitely be coming back here.

data.title: Good views of Folsom
data.text: Stopped for chips and drinks. Views of bridge over American River or historic Folsom. Restaurant has been in business since 1979.

data.title: Mexican cuisine
data.text: Hungry for Mecican food, this is the place for that quick no fringe dining.  A special lunch menu.  Salsa is mild, had to ask for their hot version for the  tortilla chips.  Variety of margarita, drinks.

data.title: Margaritas are OK, food is boring.
data.text: Visited the Hacienda many times. It is a nice place, views of Sutter Street, with a nice deck with umbrellas. The inside area is nice too. They make OK margaritas, nothing special, but OK. Problem is the food is bland with no inspiration, nothing special and presented in a ho hum fashion. Customer service is just average. Mexican food should have unique flavors with some flair and should taste authentic. When I used to go there with friends we would start at the Hacienda for margaritas and then go eat somewhere else. They have been closed for a few years due to a fire and have recently reopened. Maybe they hired a better chef, hopefully. It would be nice to have a real Mexican restaurant on Sutter Street.

data.title: Dinner
data.text: It's a great location.  Old town Folsom is awesome!!! Eating on the patio or the bar area is best.  Good service.  We ordered fajitas.  They weren't my favorite but it was nice to be back since the fire. It's a fun place to have a drink forsure!

data.title: It's Finally Open Again!
data.text: Good Mexican food in a cool environment in Old Folsom.  We enjoy the food, but love the atmosphere of eating on the deck over-looking Old Folsom.  Decent prices, good Mexican food and good atmosphere.

data.title: Sisters Night Out
data.text:
My sisters and I have a girls night out once a month. Hacienda recently reopened and we were anxious to go back. It was always good and it only got better. ALL the staff was friendly and attentive. There were 3 of us so we ordered the Carnitas for 2, Guacamole,  and the Bean Dip. All was delicious and plenty. Enough to take home. We were there during happy hour so special prices were going on. 

The  owner's Cris and Sherri have outdone themselves.

data.title: Those are some big chimichangas!
data.text: I visited here on a Friday night. It was very busy, but service was still fast and friendly. I wasn't that hungry, so I ordered the chimichangas. They looked small on the menu but that was not the case. They were really big and tasted good. The place also has a nice selection of beer.

data.title: Great Burritos!
data.text: I ate here while staying at the nearby Lake Natoma Inn. The burritos were so good that I came back later in my stay!

data.title: Come for the drinks - you will need them
data.text: The Hacienda has a pretty nice view and ample drinks.   But like many places of its ilk the food is less than good.  This is Mexican food like I have never had - not good at all.

data.title: average
data.text: the best part of this place is the deck.  drinks on the deck overlooking Sutter Street.  Food was ok..

data.title: Good mexican food
data.text: One of our favorites in folsom.  Very good food, reasonable, outdoor seating, lots of food. Nice location in folsom.

data.title: Love this place
data.text: We have been coming here for over 20 years now - before we had kids, while they were growing up and now they are on their own - staff is always very friendly - the deck is one of my favorite places to enjoy a great margarita - the menu is fun, and prices fair - I particularly like the Chimichanga's & the shredded beef taco's - happy hour is great,  will be back again soon

data.title: Typical Texmex restaurant.
data.text:
Previous reviews are poor, but we had an adequate meal.plenty of chips and spicy salsa, refilled twice. And plentiful helpings. Service adequate, not busy so maybe that helped, but 3 or 4 servers kept tables supplied.
Not from the area but friends who live here took us, and situated in an old cowboy street, with bars and art shops etc, so street worth visiting anyway.

data.title: Good food, poor service
data.text: Service started out great - and we were able to get a seat outside.  But once the waiter brought us our food, that was the last we saw of him.  No refill on soda, water or our chips.  I had to go find him to ask for a take out container, which he brought to the table.  Then we waited and waited and he never came back.  So we went and found him again to get our bill.  Poor service.

data.title: Go to Q'bole Restaurant for Mexican a Few Blocks From Here!
data.text: We're from the area, and this is one of the worst Mexican restaurants in the entire area, if not THE worst.  Although it's been some time ago, the last time we ate at this place, the food was all bland and looking and tasting like it came out of a metal can, and the margaritas were so poorly made, we couldn't drink them.  I see by current reviews that nothing has changed and it's still pretty much awful food.  Do yourself a big favor, and find your way over to Q'bole Mexican Restaurant, which isn't far down the street (easy walking distance), where you'll find a great bar and far better food and service!

data.title: Not close to what it used to be
data.text: Had not eaten here in several years so I was looking forward to a nice lunch in a familiar setting.  Boy was I disappointed.  The food which once was very good was terrible.  I couldn't finish my meal not because I was full it was that bad.  Should have known things had gone down hill as it was very quite on the outside deck for lunch and it used to always be busy.  What a waste of a nice location in Historic Folsom.   Be smart go elsewhere if you are looking for great Mexican food.

data.title: Amazing lunch specials!
data.text: Came here with a friend and was pleasantly surprised with their lunch specials. I had the chicken fajitas and they were cheap and delicious. My friend had the nachos and she loved them too. Our waiter was very attentive and nice. Definitely will be back.

data.title: Staring through the trees onto the street
data.text: Had lunch hoping it would be better than the last time, nobody there, server had to be board out of his mind came to the table every 5 minutes, very nice but we were not in a hurry and trying to talk, they just wanted us to eat and get out. Chips and salsa good the tamela was terrible I didn't eat it server didn't ask why.
